
[1]admonition

   ADMONI'TION, n. Gentle reproof; counseling against a fault; instruction
   in duties; caution; direction. Tit. 3. 1Cor. 10. In church discipline,
   public or private reproof to reclaim an offender; a step preliminary to
   excommunication.
